CRM (Customer Relationship Management) is a system used to manage customer information and interactions.
It collects data such as customer details, purchases, and communication history.
In data analysis, CRM data helps businesses understand customer behavior and preferences.
It is used to identify sales trends, customer segments, and buying patterns.
CRM analysis supports better marketing, customer service, and sales strategies.
It helps improve customer satisfaction and increase business growth through data-driven decisions.
